      "id": "PopularPost250736",
      "post_content": "Everyone here is really underestimating this card's potential. You don't have to cast it for {5}{R}{R}. At worst, this card is just a [stone rain](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=stone rain) for {1} more, so you can always play [stone rain](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=stone rain) on t3 and this on t4. However, if you're playing a dedicated land destruction deck, the kicker can come in handy. Because you can't destroy any lands prior to t3, it's hard to stop your opponent from getting a few lands out. Using this card, you can hit two lands with one card in one turn, which will help you get down your opponent's land count (and since ~50% of your deck is cheap [stone rain](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=stone rain) variants, it's unlikely that you'd need your 7th land anyway).   \nAnyway, if you're trying to make a mono-red land destruction deck, the only cards there are that always destroy a land, with no drawback to you, and that cost <5 are:  \n[Avalanche Riders](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Avalanche Riders) // [Demolish](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Demolish)  \n[Earth Rift](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Earth Rift) // autoca... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "marmaris74",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost250736\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_post\">Everyone here is really underestimating this card's potential. You don't have to cast it for {5}{R}{R}. At worst, this card is just a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"stone rain\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=stone rain\">stone rain</a> for {1} more, so you can always play <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"stone rain\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=stone rain\">stone rain</a> on t3 and this on t4. However, if you're playing a dedicated land destruction deck, the kicker can come in handy. Because you can't destroy any lands prior to t3, it's hard to stop your opponent from getting a few lands out. Using this card, you can hit two lands with one card in one turn, which will help you get down your opponent's land count (and since ~50% of your deck is cheap <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"stone rain\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=stone rain\">stone rain</a> variants, it's unlikely that you'd need your 7th land anyway). <br/>Anyway, if you're trying to make a mono-red land destruction deck, the only cards there are that always destroy a land, with no drawback to you, and that cost &lt;5 are:<br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Avalanche Riders\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Avalanche Riders\">Avalanche Riders</a>  //  <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Demolish\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Demolish\">Demolish</a><br/><a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Earth Rift\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Earth Rift\">Earth Rift</a>  //  autoca... <a href=\"javascript:void(0);\" onclick=\"ExpandPost(event, this, 250736)\">(see all)</a></span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl00_postDet